{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἕξις</b>, εως, ἡ, <br /> (ἔχω): <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> (ἔχω <i>transitive</i>) <b>having, being in possession of, possession,</b> ἐπιστήμης ἕ., opposed to κτῆσις, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 197b; νοῦ [prev. author] “Cra.” 414b; ἡ τῶν ὅπλων [prev. author] “Lg.” 625c, compare “R.” 433e, “Sph.” 247a, +others, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 1022b4 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to στέρησις,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 1055b13, 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “Πυρρώνειοι ὑποτυπώσεις” 3.49. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> in surgery, <b>posture,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “κατ᾽ ἰητρεῖον” 3; ἕ. ἢ θέσις [prev. work] 15. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> (ἔχω <i>intransitive</i>) <b>a being in a certain state, a permanent condition</b> as produced by practice (πρᾶξις), different from σχέσις (which is alterable) (see. below): <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> <b>state</b> or <b>habit</b> of body, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Aph.” 2.34, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 153b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἕ. ὑγιεινή (so also [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 1.2.4), opposed to διάθεσις ἀθλητική, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ τροφῆς” 34; σχέσις καὶ ἕ. καὶ ἡλικίη [prev. author] “Mochl.” 41; ἡ φύσις καὶ ἡ ἕ. [prev. author] “Acut.” 43: _plural_, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Sensu” 69 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: generally, <b>condition,</b> ἐν ἕξει τοῦ δρᾶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Compositione Verborum” 25; ἕ. λεπτὴ κατὰ τοῦτο τὸ μέρος 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 12; τῷ θερμὴν ἕ. ἔχοντι 3rd c.BC: Polystratus Epicureus p.26W. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>outward appearance,</b> ἡ ἕ. τοῦ σώματος κρείσσων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Dan.1.15, cf. LXX.1Ki.16.7, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Symmachus LXX.Lam.4.7\">LXX+2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>habit</b> of a vine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 3.14.5 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of material objects, ὑπὸ μιᾶς ἕξεως συνέχεσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “adversus Mathematicos” 7.102, compare 1st c.AD: Philo Judaeus 2.511, “Stoicorum Veterum Fragmenta” 2.124, +others \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.1.b</b></Level4> <i>medical</i>, <b>the system,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 2.45e, Mnesith. [prev. work] 54b, 7th c.AD: Paulus Aegineta Medicus 3.59. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>state</b> or <b>habit of mind,</b> ἕ. κακίης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 184; τὰς φύσεις τε καὶ ἕξεις τῶν ψυχῶν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 650b, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ ἐν τῇ ψυχῇ ἕ., opposed to ἡ τῶν σωμάτων ἕ., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. author] “Tht.” \">Refs</a>][same place]; πονηρᾶς ψυχῆς ἕξει[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 167b; λαμβάνειν ἕξιν τιμιωτέραν [prev. author] “R.” 591b. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.2.b</b></Level4> especially <b>acquired habit,</b> opposed to ἐνέργεια, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1098b33, +others \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>trained habit, skill,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 268e, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Problemata” 955b1, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 10.47.7, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 2.29 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τέχνη defined as ἕ. ἢ διάθεσις ἀπὸ παρατηρήσεως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 1.69S.; ἄκρα ἕ. 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Compositione Verborum” 11: with _genitive_, τὴν τῶν Ἰουδαϊκῶν γραμμάτων ἕξιν Aristeas 121; ἕ. πολιτικῶν λόγων 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 2.35 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] (Almost confined to Prose, but[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare 5th-6th c.AD: Orphica “Argonautica” 391.) \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1838","accentedUnicode":"ἕξις","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2192","matchingForm":"ἔχω","stepTransliteration":"echō","gloss":"to have/be","_zh_tw_Gloss":"有","_es_Gloss":"tener/ser","_zh_Gloss":"有"}],"shortDef":"constant use, practice habit","mediumDef":"constant use, practice habit <br /><b>a condition of body</b>, or <b>mind,</b> strictly, as resulting from practice; <b>habit,</b> <ref='Heb.5.14'>Heb. 5:14</ref>*","stepGloss":"habit/practice","stepTransliteration":"hexis","count":1,"_es_Definition":"uso, costumbre","_zh_tw_Definition":"成熟 (來 5:14)","_zh_Definition":"成熟 (来 5:14)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"luyện tập; tập quán; thói quen. Xem G2192","_zh_tw_Gloss":"習用","_es_Gloss":"hábito/práctica ","_zh_Gloss":"习用"}]}